deck_excerpt: Miragestallio is back, and we're all for it! Time for Salamangreat to turn up the heat!
deck_description: Now that Miragestallio is back, Salad builds have started to run Backup Secretary and Sea Archiver again. While this does make it easier to access Miragestallio, I think that it's not necessary, as you already have plenty of level 3s in the deck (Foxy, Spinny, Gazelle, Flame Bufferlo even) that you'll either draw or add to hand during your combos. You also only have 1 rank 3 that you'll want to go into in this strategy, that being Miragestallio. Instead, I continued to include Parallel eXceed (from earlier builds) for easy access to rank 4s (which are less accessible to this deck.) Extra deck ratios are pretty standard, just sided the usual Bagooska for Miragestallio. Also, I know I'm not running that many hand traps, but I built the deck to be more focused around playing through hand traps than using them, but I still included the best ones. Anyways, feel free to leave suggestions in the comments about how to improve on this deck, and also tell me what deck I should make next.

deck_excerpt: A big 60 card way to fill in the need parts to make Marincess competitive!
deck_description:
Marincess normally plays as a "protect the castle" type of deck. A very consistent one. Reasons therefor is mainly their field spell. Any link 3 or above Marincess monster combined with the field spell is good. The big problem is that those protection effects are only applied while the field spell stays on the field. Beyond the boss monster you are able to put up there is nothing to interact with the other player. No negates or whatsoever (Except for Marincess wave). My wish would be to get another Monster that is able to interact more... So we desperately need some way to keep our field spell on the board. Either by protecting it (Field barrier) or by interrupting the opponent. Normally the way to do this would be by putting up some negates.   We need to know just little things about this deck:
  1. Your hand is dead if you have no Marincess monster card hence why we are playing some of the trash cards (and more than one mandarine).
  2. How many Marincess monsters you need to summon one link 4 marincess monster with searching the field spell and the summoned monster needs crystal heart as material.
  3. How can I utilize the other cards to put up more protection.
  4. The magical number is level 8. (Synchro summon).
  5. The field spell only protects from the opponents effects (torrential).
  6. You have a lot of built in protections (field spell, Basilalima, Marbled rock, Wonder Heart, dont sleep on Fury of Kairyu-Shin).
A few combos you need to know:
  1. Blue Tang or Sea Horse = field spell + link 4: NS Sea Horse --> Link 1 Blue slug, effect add back Sea Horse --> SS Sea Horse --> Link 1 Sea angel, effect add field spell --> link 2 splash mage, effect special sea horse --> link 2 Coral anenome, effect reborn splash mage, activate field spell --> link4
  2. Blue Tang +  Pascalus + any extender = field spell + link 4 + toadally awesome (Careful with zone placement): NS Pascalus, effect, SS Blue Tang, pitch Sea horse --> link 1 (Blue tang) Blue Slug, effect Sea horse to hand, effect draw Blue tang (CHAINBLOCK) --> SS Sea horse --> link 1 Sea angel, effect search field spell --> link 2 Coral anenome (both link 1s), effect reborn blue tang --> XYZ Bahamut, effect SS toad --> activate field spell, link 4, effect field spell
  3. PERFECT COMBO: Pascalus + Blue Tang + (1. Instant Fusion + 2 ways for level 3 (Sea horse, Sea archiver, monster reborn, world legacy suc)/(2. Scrypton + Arboria + extender)/(3. Always have in mind that WHITE Stingray reborn can be a tuner) = field spell + link 4 + toad + Dragite: basically the same as the 2. combo but in case of 1. make sure to summon the Sea archiver when possible or just reborn + Theseus (Instant Fusion) for Dragite; 2. Arboria can be summoned at the end in a zone and scrypton should be easy too; 3. white stingray can be a tuner and therefor is + another level 4 after being reborn (Coral anenome is always a 100% reborn) is Dragite too. Extenders for that are Shthana, Silent Angler, Aqua Spirit, another Stingray, etc.
  Thinks i tried but really disliked were handtraps. They were always the keyfactor to bricking. Without handtraps there are just a few unplayable hands. It's actually good. I really hope you enjoy this build! Any ideas are welcome!

deck_description: Deck Profile, How to, Combos, and Duel Replay:  https://youtu.be/Jd7Gb91iWMY  You should focus on using Different Dimension Capsule to banish Obelisk The Tormentor so you can add it to your hand two turns from activation. During the 1st turn after that, you should focus on using the Photon Sabre Tiger or Nimble engine to get monsters on your field and protect yourself. The Nimble engine will keep your opponent busy. The second turn after you should use the Condemned Witch engine to grab a Forbidden Chalice from your deck, and then during your opponents turn activate its effect to summon Ra's Desciple, which will activate and allow you to summon two more Ra's Desciple. On your third turn if you didn't get board wiped you should have enough monsters to tribute summon for Obelisk.  Tribute summon for Obelisk earlier if you also can get Exchange Souls in hand.  Use Supply Squad to draw through your deck and the other cards to protect you and control the board. When you have used up your Nimble or condemned witch's, use Pot of Avarice to recycle them back into the deck and draw two.  Try to also time your Obelisk Summon so you can use Fist of Fate to board wipe your opponent's backrow.  Also have a blast!

To make the endboard you'll have to find a way to Special Summon Elemental HERO Shadow Mist and Vision HERO Vyon. To search for their Fusion Spells.   The usual combo looks like this. In hand: Elemental HERO Solid Soldier and Elemental HERO Shadow Mist.
  1. Normal Summon Solid Soldier, Effect, Special Summon Shadow Mist.
  2. Shadow Mist Effect, Search Mask Change.
  3. Link into Isolde, Effect, Search Elemental HERO Bubbleman on Summon.
  4. Isolde Effect send 4 Equip Spells to Summon Vision HERO Vyon.
  5. Vyon Effect send Destiny HERO Malicious. Vyon Effect Banish Solid Soldier to search Polymerization.
  6. Activate Polymerization, Sending Bubbleman and Vyon to Summon Elemental HERO Sunrise.
  7. Sunrise Effect to Search Miracle Fusion, Activate it by Banishing Bubbleman and a HERO to Summon Elemental HERO Absolute Zero
  8. Banish Malicious to Special Summon another copy and use Mask Change on it to Summon Dark Law.
Endboard is: Isolde, Dark Law, Sunrise and Absolute Zero Remember: Xtra Hero Cross Crusader Locks you Into only HEROs so you cant activate it's effect's the turn you use Fire Flint Lady or Isolde

deck_excerpt: I will continue with the YuGiOh Duel Links guide on Worm decks. This time I will discuss about other cards, additional cards, and replacement cards th
deck_description: I will continue with the YuGiOh Duel Links guide on Worm decks. This time I will discuss about other cards, additional cards, and replacement cards that you can use on the Worm deck. You can replace some cards, add cards, and even remake the Worm deck that I created in the first part of this article. You can replace all the cards in the Worm deck using all the cards that I will discuss, except the Evil Dragon Ananta card. This is because, Evil Dragon Ananta is a mainstay monster card that is in synergy with the Worm monster card. In addition, if you don't use Evil Dragon Ananta, the Worm deck is not strong enough to face other decks in the YuGiOh Duel Links game. Regarding the character's ability, you can actually replace it with all the existing character's abilities or you think are suitable. Alternative character abilities that I recommend when using the Worm deck are Yami Yugi's Destiny Draw or Joey Wheeler's Last Gamble. To find out what other cards, additional cards, and replacement cards you can use on the Worm deck, see the cards and their explanations below. A monster card that has the following effect: if flipped, you can destroy an enemy's Spell/Trap card in the field. This card is suitable for destroying/controlling the enemy's back row. If you have trouble destroying the enemy's back row before you can special summon Devil Dragon Ananta, then you can use this card first. You can get this card through the Generation Next pack gatcha. Links: https://pdx.instructure.com/eportfolios/973/Home/Ver_Rpido_y_Furioso_9_2021_Pelcula_Completa_ONLINE_GRATIS https://pdx.instructure.com/eportfolios/973/Home/Ver_Fast_and_Furious_9_2021_Pelcula_Completa_en_Espaol_Latino https://pdx.instructure.com/eportfolios/972/Home/Ver_Rpido_y_Furioso_9_2021_Pelcula_Completa_Online_LATINO_Gratis https://pdx.instructure.com/eportfolios/972/Home/Ver_Rapido_y_Furioso_9_Pelcula_Completa_2021_Online_HD_en_Espaol_Latino https://pdx.instructure.com/eportfolios/972/Home/Ver_Fast_and_Furious_9_2021_Pelcula_Completa_Online_HD_en_Espaol_Latino https://ello.co/emopp23/post/mspmqmr6zzp3d6iy_cnyng Reptile type monster card. The purpose of using this monster card is to use it as a beater, because it has a fairly high ATK, namely: 1850. One of the Reptile-type monsters that has a fairly high ATK. You can get this card through the Echoes of Silence pack gatcha. Reptile type monster card which has the following effect: if it is flipped, you can return one monster card in the field. A Reptile-type monster card that has very useful effects on you! If you have difficulty dealing with a monster card that has a high enough ATK, then you can return the monster card to the enemy's hand using this card effect. You can get this card through the Chaotic Compliance pack gatcha.

deck_excerpt: A small update to my original decklist, created as a stopgap
deck_description:
This decklist is a small update to my original concept decklist for the Solfahcord Pile, made primarily because while I have or bought all the cards featured in the original recipe, some of which (namely the handtraps and Solemn cards) are already in use in other decks. Regardless the presence of Halqlifibrax, Selene, Diviner, and especially Masquerena still means this isn't a budget deck. I decided to make this a seperate decklist as the intention will be to eventually buy the missing cards and use the original deck, or playtest the changed cards to see which ones work better. As such this is a stop gap. The primary gameplan hasn't changed, this is a control deck with a small emphasis on getting out I:P Masquerena, Absolute Dragon and a 3rd monster to summon Avramax and Vortex during the opponent's turn, While using any remaining cards in the hand to fortify the board. One possible combo is detailed my my original deck post. As for the changes, The Solemn traps are replaced by one One for One, and two each of Anti-Spell Fragrance and Heavy Storm Duster. This is mainly for another card to get Cutia out and backrow hate, respectably. For the Extra, Linkuriboh replaces Abyss Dweller as I don't have a 3rd copy of the latter yet. For the side deck I went with 1 Twin Twisters, 2 of Denko Sekka, and 3 of Effect Veiler. this is in place of the Ash and Nibiru. With Veiler as a lateral move form Ash and Sekka and Twisters being more backrow hate for the recently empowered Sky Striker matchup, as well as Pendulum deck (such as the mirror) and trap-heavy decks like Eldlitch (since Sekka blocks Traps)   Minor updates would warrant changing this list, directly, while more substantial updates (being it adjusting for the banlist or changing out 7 or more cards in total) would parent a new iteration which would be labeled 0.2 or 1.0 depending on how tournament ready (Locals mainly) I think this list is.
EDIT: -2 Denko Sekka, -2 Anti-Spell Fragerance +1 Trias Hierarchia, +1 Called by the Grave. +2 Archfiend Eccentrick

Hello.  Frist of all i won`t explain the standart Lyrilusc Tri-Brigade combos there are enough Youtuber`s that do that, i rather focus on the cards that are unusual in this deck.  The only thing i will say is <u>don`t</u> use Fraktall to send Kit to the Gy and then send Nervall and then search 4 something.  Just use Fraktall to send Nervall and then search and in the 1st turn u most likely want to search Kit and NS her.  So now to the unusal cards in this deck.  Main Deck:  Danger Thunderbrid/ Jackalope  Thunderbird is the Wingedbeast extender that u somtimes need and Jackalope can SS him from the deck and also u can pop a set card with it if u play u`r hand out first.  Jackalope can be searched with Shuraig and is also a target 4 Rescue Cat waht somtimes will come in handy.  Reborn Tengu:  Can SS a other Kopie from the Deck (<u>not</u> once per turn) can get u to high Link`s very esay and fuels the GY.  Can be searched with Tenki and SS from the deck with Airborne.  And i know u can draw 2 ore 3 Kopies of it but keep in mind this is a 50 card deck so it won`t happend that much.  Simorgh of the Beginning:  If u really need a Wingedbeast or lvl 1 on the Field u can send him from the deck to the GY an SS him but keep in mind that he locks u under Wingedbeast.  He also can protect Simorgh bird of sovereignty because of the eff of Simorgh bird of sovereignty.  Can also be SS with the eff of Simorgh of the Kings.  Watch Cat:  Is importent 4 Ariborne because of the low ATK of Lyrilusc mons and Nervall so u always have a traget in the deck to SS.  Is a traget 4 Rescue Cat  A free lvl 1 extender.  U leave it on the field if u dont need it to bann it in the EP and search Tenki 4 the next turn.  Extra Deck:  2x Shuraig 2x Ferrijit 2x Simorgh bird of sovereignty:  Because u`r board can be broken and this deck is not a Glasscannon. Playing 2 of each of them will help u build up u`r board agian and gain the control of the field back.  Cross Sheep:  Is the Link that u just  want to summon if u just need a link 2 and if u summoned Gamma and Driver in ur turn because u dont have a other easy way to use them but if u want to do that keep in mind to do that before u use the Linksummon eff from one off ur Tri-Brigade mons.  Side Deck:  Archnemeses Eschatos:  U only want to side him in Game 2 or 3 when u know that u`r going 2nd or u`r going first and u`r opponent is playing a dragon deck because the eff only works with types that are on the field. But it is very powerful it can nuke u`r opponents board and lock him so he can`t summon.  Spiritualism:  The beast way to out Spells and Traps that are strong agianst this deck like Zombieworld or Mine it don`t taget, don`t destroys and can`t be negated.  There is no way that u`r opponent can protect his spells/traps from this card, it will gives u 1 turn and this is all waht u need.  The rest of the deck is common stuff. Dr.Deck     The "Mass Effect" games have had several film adaptations underway, which have never started. However, it can still become a reality. About a month ago, the collection "Mass Effect: Legendary Edition" landed, which are nicer versions of the beloved science fiction trilogy. https://oss1173filmguide.wildapricot.org/ In an interview with the site Business Insider, project manager Mac Walters says that several film adaptations of the games have been underway, but have failed. https://conjuring3deutschguide.wildapricot.org/ Also read: 5 games that should be a movie or TV series As early as 2010, a "Mass Effect" film was announced by Legendary Pictures, which never materialized. Walters says that one of the difficulties was to compress the expansive and story-heavy universe in a film. https://thesuicidesquaddeutschguide.wildapricot.org/ - It felt like we were always fighting headwinds with the franchise. What story do you tell in 90-120 minutes? Instead of a film, the project was transformed into a TV series, which also did not lift from idea to reality. Mac Walters says, however, that this does not mean that it will never get rid of, but rather that it is a matter of time before it becomes a film or TV series of "Mass Effect". - It's more about when, than about. It is such a vast world and so many in the TV and film industry have asked us if we want to do it and said that we really should do it, he says. https://spacejam2deutschguide.wildapricot.org/ The first "Mass Effect" was released in 2007 and is about the human soldier Shepherd, who together with an ensemble of interesting types goes into space to defeat the synthetic Reaper creatures who want to kill all biological life in the universe. deck_excerpt: I should’ve not picked a earth machine deck
deck_description: Geargia is one of the older earth machine decks out there.  It got its own structure deck but it started earlier than that, it first debuted with the monster geargiano who was in Generation Force, the was the only card of the archetype at the time and didn’t have specific name listing so it wasn’t an archetype quite yet. Later it got actual support in Rise of the Duelist. Later they would go to get their own structure deck, and, despite never taking off too far, got their own little following. But they’re also known to be pretty bad, sure they got monster spam but they also are pretty underwhelming these days, but here we are! Earth machines to save the day! With all of the new earth machine cards making machina one of the better decks in the game I decided to use that for geargia, I took an ancient gear spin to make the deck have a little more brute force and trains for an OTK swing, I could’ve added more but I felt that then it wouldn’t be a Geargia deck anymore.

The deck is really just made for casual play but the combo of Shadow Vampire + Vampire Duke is a fun one and then you get Bram out on the field.  Then, if you activate Vampire's Domain and then summon Vampire Red Baron, activate Domain to normal summon Scourge and then use his ability to bring Baron back? That gives you your ace monster, Vampire Sheridan and there's a few fun things that can do from there depending on the stage that the duel is at.  The Retainer and Familiar play on sending your own Vampire cards to the graveyard so Voivode is one of the first ones you'll want to try to send there if you can because when you use Bram's effect to special summon monsters from your opponent's grave, it's easy to get Voivode out on the field. Then, if you use Bram and Vampire Sucker's effects on the same turn, you can just sacrifice 2 of your opponents special summoned monsters to get Voivode out on the field so you don't have to sacrifice your own monsters.  Just a deck for casual play but I have fun with it

deck_excerpt: A Dark Magician and Dark Magician Girl Fusion Deck.
deck_description: A Dark Magician and Dark Magician Girl fusion deck. "Dark Magical Circle" and "Magician Navigation" are key multi-purpose tools. DMC: draw power + banishing, makes use of cards whose name become "Dark Magician" including: "Magician of Dark Illusion" (field) and "Dark Magician the Dragon Knight" (field or graveyard, synergy with "Eternal Soul" and "Magicians' Combination"). MN: summons 2 and can banish itself from the graveyard to negate a spell/trap "The Eye of Timaeus" and "Secrets of Dark Magic", along with "Magicalized Fusion", for fusion summons. Eye uses only one DM or DMG from the field to bring out a range of fusion monsters. Secrets uses material from the hand or field, bring out "The Dark Magicians" or "Quintet Magician". MF is not searchable like the rest of the cards in this deck, however being able to use material from the field or graveyard is quite useful. "Soul Servant" quickplay spell place 1 card that is or lists DM or DMG from the hand, deck, or graveyard to the top of the deck. Can banish itself from the graveyard to draw cards based on the number of different DM and DMG on field and graveyard. Basically a Pot of Greed when used properly. "Magician's Rod" normal summon to grab a DM spell/trap from the deck. Tribute a Spellcaster to add MR back to the hand from the GY.  "Magicians' Souls" can send up to 2 Spells/Traps from your hand and/or field to the GY: draw that many cards. Discard a lvl 6+ spellcaster from the deck to activate: Can be special summoned or Send to the GY from the hand in order to summon DM or DMG from the GY. 0 ATK/DEF card with great utility.

deck_excerpt: Here is the updated version of my Mayakashi deck after my 1st locals. Feel free to leave suggestions on how I can improve the deck.
deck_description: Hello everyone, its very nice to see you guys again and I hope you guys are keeping safe during these times. So just recently I've attended my first yugioh locals and it was a pretty fun and interesting experience for myself even though I didn't expect to perform well I still got the chance to learn from my mistakes whilst trying to improve & tweak the deck a little bit.  So far I've made a few adjustments to the deck such as adding Jack-o-bolan for more GY extenders as well as a copy of Drowning Mirror force to the deck. At the moment I am planning on making the deck competitive being that its the only deck that I am playing at this point and personally I don't see myself playing different deck such as the Mayakashi. However my best friend Zoroark_Gaming was luckily enough to pull 1 copy of Eldlich the Golden Lord from Maximum Gold recently and from there I thought to myself that maybe there is a chance I can make this deck more competitive once I've figured out a well balanced ratio for the deck as well as I am thinking of replacing a copy of Oboro-Guruma, the Wheeled Mayakashi for a copy of Draconecro Nethersoul Dragon in future builds of the deck.     I would love to hear your guys thoughts and suggestions on how I can improve my Mayakashi deck as well as what cards should be taken out and replaced with and also what ratio of cards that I could play to make the deck more balanced.

We can start with progression series, here is our discord if you want to join us, all the rules are there: https://discord.gg/XvWJ6sZHbZ  This is how my luck started(prety bad), I hope you will be more lucky while opening 24 packs of lob packs.

deck_excerpt: Use Fortune Ladies as an engine to draw Exodia !
deck_description: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wP6qtAK_vaA  Use Fortune Ladies as a draw engine to get Exodia in one turn.  The main combo is to get light+past on the field, to banish light with past to get Water from the deck and draw 2. From there on, you need to synchro and then de-synchro with your fortune ladies to keep spamming Fortune Lady Water's draw 2 effect, until you find a card that'll let you summon a second FL Water.  Once you have 2 FL Waters in rotation, you can start making Lv9 Synchros like Ravenous Crocosaur and Trishula, and then draw 4 every time you de-synchro.  For an example, check near the end of the video (timestamps are in the description).

deck_description: This deck is about pumping out as many Blue-Eyes as posible in order to make rank 8 monsters or level 9 synchros, this is accomplished by using the stone's effects to summon stuff from the deck, summoning your Blue-Eyes from your hand with the Blue-Eyes Alternative White Dragon or Nebula Dragon, and/or sending them to the GY to revive them with the revival spells or the Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon. To speed up your deck and trigger the stones effects, as well as having a target to revive, you have the draw-two spells (Trade-In and Cards of Consonance). You find monster removal in the Blue-Eyes Alternative White Dragon and backrow removal in the Dragon Spirit of White, and both on your extra deck monsters. To disrupt your opponent you have Ash Blossom and the rank 8 monsters, and to protect your monsters you have Blue-Eyes Spirit Dragon and it's toolbox, Forbidden Lance and ocasionally Return of the Dragon Lords.
Ultimate Fusion Blue-Eyes Deck

deck_name: Sky Strikers w/ Kaiju (Post Banlist) - June 2021
deck_description:
Anyone who likes giant monsters and girls in mechs has come to the right place. Welcome. ENGAGE is back, expanding the Sky Striker's toolset. Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! is a spell for Sky Strikers that searches any card besides itself, and lets you draw 1 if you have 3 spells or more in your GY. Crazy, isn't it? For first time Sky Striker players, this deck may prove to be challenging, but fear not, because I will help you along the way! Let's engage! I have been playing Sky Strikers since its release in 2019, and I have to say it is one of the most fun and rewarding decks to play if done right. It certainly plays out a lot of cards at once, so newcomers to YuGiOh may not know what to do with all of the combos. Here are some examples: Sky Strikers go first:  For this starting hand we have: Multirole, Area Zero/Terraforming, Roze, and There Can Be Only One
  • Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole > Destroys Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero > SS Sky Striker Ace - Raye > Link Sky Striker Ace - Kagari > Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero to hand > Play Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero
  • Play There Can Be Only One
  • SS Sky Striker Ace - Roze
OR
  • Sky Striker Ace - Raye > Link Sky Striker Ace - Shizuku > End And Search Sky Striker (Any Spell)
So, even though it's not shown, there are many different variations of just 1 turn with 5 cards. Sky Strikers can be extremely powerful in 1:1 exchanges and can be further empowered by Kaiju support. I believe that running 2 of any Kaiju (I prefer Gameciel and Gardala) could work as a helpful support. Running 3 is okay, so long as you have the space for it. I also run a Kyoutou Waterfront here because the effects that come with Kaiju cards could greatly benefit Sky Striker gameplay. Especially Gameciel's. Why do I run Summon Limit? Because it's simply a good stall tool, but obviously you don't need to run it always. Try Mystic Mine if you don't like people getting advantages. There Can Be Only One simply just helps against a variety of different types of decks. You might want to switch out against decks like Dragon Link and Dinosaur, though. Upstart Goblin gives you a good +1 for extra resources. Sure, it may give them 1000 LP, but no one really cares when you have their board wiped out. Called By The Grave is a good counter to Ghost Girls. ROTA helps get out Raye or Roze. Cosmic Cyclone because some spells can be pesky. Forbidden Droplet because of its power and utility in the current meta. Accesscode for smashing other people's monsters. There are many decks for Sky Strikers, but it's up to you to find a deck that works for you. I hope this helps. Thank you! See you next time!
